 :tx/rationale "AUDIT-PERF-3: transact() allocates O(E) HashSet on every call. store.rs:1334 creates pre_existing HashSet by collecting entity_index.keys().copied(). With 10K entities, this copies 10K EntityIds (32 bytes each) = ~320KB allocation per transaction, even for inserting 1 datom. SOLUTION: Replace with direct entity_index.contains_key() check per datom in the transaction. The pre_existing set is used only to detect new entities (line 1388-1394). Instead of building the full set, check each datom entity against entity_index on the fly. VERIFICATION: Benchmark transact() before/after. Verify no behavior change via existing test suite. DEPENDENCIES: Independent. Minor optimization."
